Privacy Policy — Chonky Browser

Last updated: [14.08.2025]

1. Introduction

Chonky Browser is a lightweight web browser created using MIT App Inventor.
Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how our app handles information.

2. Information We Collect

We do not collect, store, process, or share any personal information from users.
The app does not require you to create an account and does not use analytics, advertising, or tracking technologies.

3. Browsing Data

All browsing history, cookies, and cached files are stored only on your device during your active session.

This data is automatically deleted when you close the app.

We do not transmit any browsing data to our servers (we have no servers).

4. Third-Party Websites

Our browser can open third-party websites such as Google Search, Wikipedia, and others.
These websites may collect information according to their own privacy policies.
We have no control over and are not responsible for how third-party sites handle your data.

5. Security

The app uses HTTPS whenever supported by the visited site to help protect your data in transit.

Android WebView Safe Browsing is enabled to warn about potentially unsafe pages.

6. Children’s Privacy

Chonky Browser is not directed to children under 13 years old.
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

7. Changes to This Policy

If we make changes to this Privacy Policy, we will update the “Last updated” date above.
The updated policy will be available both in the app and on our website.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
tolsticup@gmail.com
